      <mj-section>
        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-text>
            <h4>Bike to Work Day -  Have Breakfast @ KGNU June 28th!</h4>
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
        <mj-column width="35%">
          <mj-image src="http://objects-us-west-1.dream.io/email-images/june-17/bike-to-work-17.jpg" href="http://objects-us-west-1.dream.io/email-images/june-17/bike-to-work-17.jpg"/>
        </mj-column>
        <mj-column width="65%">
          <mj-text>
            <a href="https://communitycycles.org/about/">Community Cycles</a> has organized more than 60 local businesses in Boulder to host breakfast and bike service stations to serve food and drinks for commuters on <span class="date">June 28th</span> for <strong>Bike to Work Day</strong> from 6:30 to 9 a.m. KGNU is one of the breakfast stations!  Come win tickets to a concert or an annual membership and go on a tour to see how what you hear on air is made.<br><br>Ride (or walk) by our Boulder station at 4700 Walnut St. for breakfast <span class="date">June 28th</span>, we’d love to see you!
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
      </mj-section>

      <mj-section>

        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-text>
            <h4>KGNU's 29th Annual Charles Sawtelle Memorial Mountain Jam</h4>
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
        <mj-column width="35%">
          <mj-image src="http://objects-us-west-1.dream.io/email-images/june-17/kgnu-charles-2017.jpg" href="http://objects-us-west-1.dream.io/email-images/june-17/kgnu-charles-2017.jpg" />
        </mj-column>

        <mj-column width="65%">
          <mj-text>
            <strong>With <a href="http://laurielewis.com/">Laurie Lewis &amp; The Right Hands</a>, <a href="http://www.masontownmusic.com/">Masontown</a>, and <a href="https://thunderandrainmusic.com/">Thunder and Rain</a></strong><br>
            <p><strong>"The Charles"</strong>, a KGNU tradition, is a family-friendly event for music fans who enjoy clear mountain air, dazzling acoustic music, and great food in a spectacular setting. The festivities get started at 11:30am and run until 4:30pm on <span class="date">Sunday, July 23rd</span>.</p>
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>

      <mj-column width="35%">
        <mj-image src="http://www.brownpapertickets.com/g/6/BPT_buy_tickets_large.png" href="http://www.brownpapertickets.com/event/2949345" width="182px"/>
      </mj-column>

      <mj-column width="65%">
        <mj-text>
          Tickets are <strong>&#36;20</strong> for KGNU members, <strong>&#36;25</strong> for non-members and are available <a href="http://thecharles2017.brownpapertickets.com">online</a> or by calling KGNU at 303-449-4885 weekdays between 9:00am and 5:00pm. Tickets &#36;5 more day of show. Children 12 and under are free. Food and beverages are available for purchase. No pets or coolers.
        </mj-text>

      </mj-section>

      <mj-section>
        <mj-column width="100%">
