            <h3>News Updates</h3>

            <h4>KGNU and the League of Women Voters of Boulder County</h4>
            <p>KGNU is partnering with the League of Women Voters of Boulder County on a  vmonthly commentary series called Making Democracy Work for All! which focuses on educating listeners on the workings of state and local government and letting them know how they can get involved at different stages of the political process. This month Mary Anna Dunn, Health Care Team Leader for the League of Women Voters of Boulder County, shares some thoughts about mental wellness. Click <a href="http://news.kgnu.org/2017/06/making-democracy-work-for-all-mental-health/">here</a> to read more.</p>

            <h4>Laura Flanders Returns to KGNU</h4>
            <p>The show has started broadcasting on Friday afternoons at 3.30pm on KGNU, in place of FSRN the weekly edition, which discontinued production in April.</p>
            <p>Laura Flanders is no stranger to the KGNU airwaves as the former host of Counterspin and regular guest on other news shows from Democracy Now to Economic Update.</p>
            <p>"The Laura Flanders show stars the people I think of as the brightest, forward thinkers from the worlds of arts, activism and entrepreneurship. People who have real reality based strategies and models for power shifting change.""</p>
            Click <A href="http://news.kgnu.org/2017/06/laura-flanders-returns-to-kgnu/">here</a> to read more.

            <h4>KGNU &amp; Boulder Bookstore Radio Bookclub</h4>
            <p>KGNU is partnering with the Boulder Bookstore for our radio bookclub. Every month Arsen Kashkashian, head buyer at the Boulder Bookstore, selects a book to inspire the KGNU listening audience to read along together. We will then be joined live in studio by the author for a book discussion.</p>

            <p>To celebrate Independent Bookstore day in April, we taped the bookclub at the Boulder Bookstore with author Peter Heller. This was Peter’s second visit, previously he joined us to talk about his novel The Painter.  This time he discussed his new book Celine. Click <a href="http://news.kgnu.org/2017/05/radio-bookclub-peter-heller-and-celine/">here</a> to listen to the interview.</p>

            <p>July’s selection is Alexandra Fuller’s latest book: <a href="http://www.boulderbookstore.net/event/alexandra-fuller-quiet-until-thaw">Quiet Until the Thaw</a>. Tune in on <span class="date">Thursday July 27th</span> at 9am to hear Fuller’s interview at the bookclub.</p>
            </mj-text>
